{{Infobox organization |name = Bangladesh Haor and Wetland Development Board |image = |image_border = |size = |alt = |caption = |map = |msize = |malt = |mcaption = |abbreviation = |motto = |formation = 2000 |extinction = |type = |status = |purpose = |headquarters = [[Faridpur Sadar Upazila|Faridpur]], [[Bangladesh]] |location = |coords = <!-- Coordinates of location using a coordinates template --> |region_served = Bangladesh |members = |language = Bengali |leader_title = |leader_name = |main_organ = |parent_organization = |affiliations = |num_staff = |num_volunteers = |budget = |website = [http://bhwdb.gov.bd/ Bangladesh Haor and Wetland Development Board] |remarks = }}
'''Bangladesh Haor and Wetland Development Board''' or is a government board that is responsible for the management and regulation of Wetlands and [[Haor]]s in Bangladesh and is located in [[Dhaka]], [[Bangladesh]].<ref name="efs">{{cite web|title=About BHWDB|url=http://bhwdb.gov.bd/about|website=Department of Bangladesh Haor and Wetland Development|accessdate=21 November 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=PM for proper utilisation of wetlands|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/backpage/pm-proper-utilisation-wetlands-1219405|website=thedailystar.net|publisher=The Daily Star|accessdate=21 November 2016|date=6 May 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Sorry tale of haor people|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/backpage/sorry-tale-haor-people-158407|website=thedailystar.net|publisher=The Daily Star|accessdate=21 November 2016|date=17 October 2015}}</ref>
==History== The Government of Bangladesh passed an ordinance which formed the Haor Development Board on 22 February 1977. On 11 September 2000 it was reconstituted to form the Bangladesh Haor and Wetland Development Board by presidential order.<ref name="efs"></ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Haor-wetland board to be autonomous|url=http://archive.dhakatribune.com/bangladesh/2014/sep/25/haor-wetland-board-be-autonomous|website=archive.dhakatribune.com|publisher=Dhaka Tribune|accessdate=21 November 2016}}</ref>
